<h1>US Pints to Litres Conversions (pt to l)</h1>
<p>US recipes often specify a pint or two pints of water, milk or other liq=
uid ingredients the converters below allow you to convert these
values into litres and for European recipes from litres into US pints. The =
following link gives=20
<a href=3D"https://www.cookingconversions.org/uspintstoimperialpints.htm">C=
onversions for US pints to Imperial pints</a>. For converting
smaller amounts of liquid, generally specified in fluid ounces or millilitr=
es, we have a <a href=3D"https://www.cookingconversions.org/usfloztoml.htm"=
>US fluid ounces to=20
millilitres converter</a> and a <a href=3D"https://www.cookingconversions.o=
rg/usfloztoimperialfloz.htm">US fluid ounce to Imperial fluid ounce
converter</a>.</p>=20

